    <div class="formCard" id="ams" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">🔗 AMS Slots (Printer Mapping)</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p>
                The <strong>AMS</strong> page displays Automatic Material System (AMS) devices and their slots reported by your BambuLab printer.
                Use this page to map physical AMS slots to filaments in your inventory so the app can show which spool is loaded where.
            </p>

            <h3>How it works:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The app listens for AMS data from your printer via MQTT and shows each AMS unit and its slots.</li>
                <li>Each slot shows material, humidity and temperature when available.</li>
                <li>Use the dropdown on each slot to assign an inventory filament (or create a new one).</li>
                <li>When assigned, the filament's color preview and type appear next to the slot.</li>
                <li>You can optionally persist printer spool IDs to your spools (coming feature) so assignments survive spool swaps.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Best practices:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Auto-match attempts to match by brand/type/color. Review matches before saving.</li>
                <li>If your printer provides a stable spool External ID, store it on the spool for reliable mapping.</li>
                <li>Use the AMS page to quickly identify which physical slot a filament is loaded into when changing spools.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                <em>Tip: Open the AMS page after connecting to the printer. AMS devices update automatically as the printer reports them.</em>
            </p>

            <div style="margin-top:12px; text-align:right;">
                <a href="#toc" class="helpNavLink" style="display:inline-block; width:auto;">⬆ Back to Table of Contents</a>
