    <div class="formCard" id="faq" style="scroll-margin-top: 20px;">
        <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">❓ Troubleshooting & FAQ</h2>
        <div style="color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8;">
            <p><strong>Q: My filaments aren't showing up</strong></p>
            <p>A: Check your filters and search. You might have:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>A search term active - clear the search box</li>
                    <li>A type filter active (e.g., showing only PLA) - select "All Types"</li>
                    <li>"Low Only" enabled - toggle it off to see all filaments</li>
                </ul>
            
            <p><strong>Q: The colors don't match my actual filament</strong></p>
            <p>A: Edit the filament and update the color code. You can:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Find hex codes online or use a color picker tool</li>
                    <li>Take a photo and use an online hex color picker</li>
                    <li>Check the manufacturer's website for official color codes</li>
                </ul>
            
            <p><strong>Q: I accidentally deleted a filament</strong></p>
            <p>A: Unfortunately, deletions are permanent. However:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>If you have a CSV export backup, you can re-import it</li>
                    <li>Tip: Export your data regularly as a safety backup</li>
                </ul>
            
            <p><strong>Q: Multiple spools aren't grouping together</strong></p>
            <p>A: They only group if ALL these fields are EXACTLY the same:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Brand (case-sensitive)</li>
                    <li>Type (PLA, PETG, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Finish/Variant (Matte, Silk, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Color Name</li>
                    <li>Color Code</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Check for typos, extra spaces, or different capitalization. To fix, edit one filament to match the other exactly.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Q: How do I change the warning thresholds?</strong></p>
            <p>A: Go to Settings → Stock Thresholds section:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Enter your desired Low Threshold (yellow warning)</li>
                    <li>Enter your desired Critical Threshold (red alert)</li>
                    <li>Critical must be less than Low</li>
                    <li>Click "Save Thresholds" - changes apply immediately!</li>
                </ul>
            
            <p><strong>Q: My brand doesn't appear in the dropdown</strong></p>
            <p>A: Select "➕ Other (Add Custom)" at the bottom of the Brand dropdown, then type your custom brand name. It will be saved automatically and appear in the dropdown for future use.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Q: Can I delete a brand without deleting my filaments?</strong></p>
            <p>A: Yes! Go to Settings → Manage Brands section. Deleting a brand only removes it from the dropdown menu. Your existing filaments with that brand remain untouched.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Q: What happens when a reusable spool empties?</strong></p>
            <p>A: When a filament's weight reaches 0g and it's marked as reusable, the app automatically marks that spool as "Available" in your Spools page. You can then use it for refills!</p>
            
            <p><strong>Q: How does the color brightness sort work?</strong></p>
            <p>A: The app analyzes the hex color code and calculates perceived brightness using the standard RGB formula (accounting for how human eyes perceive different colors). Dark→Light shows blacks first, Light→Dark shows whites first.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Q: Can I track filaments by weight other than grams?</strong></p>
            <p>A: Currently the app only supports grams. If you have weights in other units:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ounces to grams: multiply by 28.35</li>
                    <li>Pounds to grams: multiply by 453.59</li>
                    <li>Kilograms to grams: multiply by 1000</li>
                </ul>
            
            <p><strong>Q: Where is my data stored?</strong></p>
            <p>A: All data is stored in a local SQLite database file on your computer. Nothing is sent to the cloud unless you manually export a CSV file. Your data is completely private and offline.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

